# SEQUENCE 09 — THE QUESTIONS OF TRUTH

/* TRACE: FU-050 | SC-031 */

EXT. ROAD AWAY FROM THE COAST — DAY #60#

Manimekalai travels inland with Aravana Adigal.

She has carried a miracle.

Now she must understand a world that cannot be healed by miracles alone.

/* TRACE: FU-051 | SC-032 */

EXT. VANJI — KNOWLEDGE COURT — DAY #61#

Teachers from different traditions gather.

Manimekalai does not enter as a victor.

She listens.

Each speaker presents the strongest form of their reasoning.

The question is not who wins.

The question is what each explanation can reveal.

/* TRACE: FU-052 | SC-033 */

INT. VANJI ASSEMBLY — LATER #62#

A materialist teacher challenges unseen claims.

TEACHER
What cannot be experienced cannot become certain merely because people desire it.

MANIMEKALAI
And what if experience itself teaches us that our senses have limits?

The room becomes quiet.

The debate changes from belief to method.

/* TRACE: FU-053 | SC-034 */

EXT. VANJI STREET — EVENING #63#

The arguments leave the hall.

A merchant measures grain.

A mother waits for medicine.

A child asks why suffering exists.

Manimekalai sees that philosophy is tested by ordinary life.

/* TRACE: FU-054 | SC-035 */

INT. ARAVANA ADIGAL'S RESTING PLACE — NIGHT #64#

ARAVANA ADIGAL places a lamp, a sealed vessel and a footprint before her.

ARAVANA ADIGAL
What do you know?

MANIMEKALAI
Only what I have examined honestly.

/* TRACE: FU-055 | SC-036 */

EXT. KANCHI — FAMINE DISTRICT — DAY #65#

The lesson becomes real.

Hunger is not only absence of food.

It is absence of systems that carry food to people.

Manimekalai sees the next question waiting.

Not what can the bowl produce?

What can people build together?

END SEQUENCE 09